WEBVTT

00:02.225 --> 00:03.265
-Previously on "Shut Eye"...

00:03.266 --> 00:04.426
-If you can't produce...

00:04.427 --> 00:05.788
-I can.

00:05.789 --> 00:07.429
-I got plenty others.

00:07.430 --> 00:08.711
What's this?

00:08.712 --> 00:10.032
-Nadine Davies.

00:10.033 --> 00:12.314
We have a very big whale
on our hands.

00:12.315 --> 00:13.676
-What about Fonso?

00:13.677 --> 00:15.477
-I'm done being someone's bitch.

00:15.478 --> 00:17.119
-You think Amraya?

00:17.120 --> 00:18.801
- They did tell her
there was a curse on her money.

00:18.802 --> 00:21.043
The Roma people...
If you're not one of them,

00:21.044 --> 00:24.366
they will happily trick you
out of every cent you have.

00:24.367 --> 00:26.649
- We've seen
some very nasty tricks.

00:26.650 --> 00:28.330
Aah!

00:28.331 --> 00:30.773
- You know, I'm an ordinary guy
and I don't do drugs.

00:30.774 --> 00:33.375
What happened to me,
this kind of brain injury,

00:33.376 --> 00:35.177
could it change
the way I see things?

00:35.178 --> 00:36.499
Colors are too bright.

00:36.500 --> 00:37.820
-Give me that pencil!

00:37.821 --> 00:40.262
- I'm hearing things.
- No, you don't!

00:40.263 --> 00:42.625
- With head injuries,
there's just no rule book.

00:42.626 --> 00:45.668
- Glad you didn't bring
your husband this time.

00:45.669 --> 00:46.829
-Fuckin' Gina.

00:46.830 --> 00:48.871
Yeah, Fonso.

00:48.872 --> 00:50.152
You're not gonna believe this.

00:50.153 --> 00:51.514
-I needed to know.

00:51.515 --> 00:54.276
Was I ever gonna find
my one true love?

00:54.277 --> 00:56.559
- Asshole put himself
in the commercial.

00:56.560 --> 00:58.200
-Make fun,

00:58.201 --> 01:01.043
but White Tony is raking it in
down there in South Bay.

01:01.044 --> 01:03.686
- The guy frying,
and he's gonna tell me

01:03.687 --> 01:05.968
that he had nothing to do
with any drive by.

01:05.969 --> 01:07.851
-He's lying.
-Who the fuck are you,
I'm lying?

01:09.813 --> 01:12.375
[ Screams ]

01:14.000 --> 01:20.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:26.349 --> 01:28.070
-Hey.

01:28.071 --> 01:29.592
I didn't hear you
come in last night.

01:29.593 --> 01:30.713
-Yeah, it was pretty late.

01:30.714 --> 01:31.714
I didn't want to wake you,

01:31.715 --> 01:34.156
so I slept on the couch.

01:34.157 --> 01:36.198
This cereal tastes strange.

01:36.199 --> 01:37.880
Like, metallic.

01:37.881 --> 01:40.242
Tastes like ball bearings.

01:40.243 --> 01:42.926
-How'd it go with Eduardo?

01:48.211 --> 01:50.573
-The kid was lying.

01:50.574 --> 01:53.095
-Who was?

01:53.096 --> 01:55.738
-I don't even know his name.

01:55.739 --> 01:58.581
But he was making way too much
eye contact.

01:58.582 --> 02:00.422
He pulled on his earlobe

02:00.423 --> 02:04.266
and he put a sack of flour
in between him and Eduardo.

02:04.267 --> 02:06.348
It was obvious.

02:06.349 --> 02:09.672
I was trying to just
keep my client on the hook.

02:09.673 --> 02:11.875
And all I said was,
"He's lying."

02:19.242 --> 02:22.045
Eduardo killed him.

02:24.007 --> 02:26.689
-Honey, that's not your fault.

02:26.690 --> 02:31.293
You didn't know
that was gonna happen.

02:31.294 --> 02:32.815
-[ Chuckles ]

02:32.816 --> 02:34.056
You're right.

02:34.057 --> 02:35.618
-Hey.

02:35.619 --> 02:39.261
We knew Eduardo was
into some bad shit.

02:39.262 --> 02:41.584
Put it out of your head.

02:41.585 --> 02:44.347
He's the kind of man who knows
how to cover his tracks.

02:46.790 --> 02:50.392
- You remember the first time
we ever had a real conversation?

02:50.393 --> 02:53.916
I think it was the third time
I had come into the club.

02:53.917 --> 02:57.079
- You told me you could
make an elephant disappear.

02:57.080 --> 03:01.243
Then you asked me
if I believed that.

03:01.244 --> 03:05.287
- And you said
you didn't believe in anything.

03:05.288 --> 03:09.572
And it was that moment I knew
I would fall in love with you.

03:09.573 --> 03:12.294
You didn't say, "Bullshit."

03:12.295 --> 03:14.737
You didn't say,
"Wow, how do you do that?"

03:14.738 --> 03:17.580
You said, "I don't believe."

03:17.581 --> 03:20.063
And I did fall in love with you.

03:22.506 --> 03:24.708
I love you, Linda.

03:26.389 --> 03:28.390
And every choice I make,

03:28.391 --> 03:30.993
everything I do,

03:30.994 --> 03:33.436
it's all for you.

03:34.598 --> 03:36.359
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

03:43.446 --> 03:44.808
[ Sighs ]

03:55.418 --> 03:57.339
-Hello?

03:57.340 --> 03:59.822
Hi, Nadine.

03:59.823 --> 04:01.464
How are you?

04:03.827 --> 04:05.748
Oh, Jesus.

04:05.749 --> 04:08.671
So sorry to hear that.

04:08.672 --> 04:11.393
Of course.

04:11.394 --> 04:13.155
Let me just wake Charlie.

04:13.156 --> 04:15.117
We'll be right over.

04:15.118 --> 04:16.398
Okay.

04:16.399 --> 04:18.921
Bye-bye.

04:18.922 --> 04:21.043
♫♫

04:21.043 --> 04:23.086
We have to get dressed.

04:26.169 --> 04:28.170
-What did the police say?

04:28.171 --> 04:30.012
- That the tree
hadn't been tampered with

04:30.013 --> 04:32.175
and there was no sign
of a break-in.

04:33.897 --> 04:37.059
- Tie this around a branch,
attach a chain to a bumper,

04:37.060 --> 04:39.822
and you could pull that tree
down without a mark.

04:39.823 --> 04:42.264
Did you set the alarm
before you went to bed?

04:42.265 --> 04:43.746
-W-Well, of course.

04:43.747 --> 04:46.268
-Your alarm code is 72856.

04:46.269 --> 04:47.590
-How do you know?

04:47.591 --> 04:49.271
- I Googled
your husband's birthday.

04:49.272 --> 04:50.713
I had a feeling
he was kind of vain.

04:50.714 --> 04:52.555
-These bastards are serious.

04:52.556 --> 04:55.157
- When you broke it off with
this woman, the fortune teller,

04:55.158 --> 04:56.839
did she ask for more money?

04:56.840 --> 04:58.360
-$10,000.

04:58.361 --> 05:00.523
She said it was severance pay.

05:00.524 --> 05:02.404
-Give her $20,000.

05:02.405 --> 05:04.126
- What?
- You give them the $10,000,

05:04.127 --> 05:05.568
they'll be back in a month
for more.

05:05.569 --> 05:06.769
-We've seen that happen.

05:06.770 --> 05:08.370
More than once, I'm afraid.

05:08.371 --> 05:11.734
- What I can make sure of
is this is a one-time situation,

05:11.735 --> 05:13.616
that they don't
keep coming back.

05:13.617 --> 05:15.337
-How do you do that?

05:15.338 --> 05:18.300
- I know a cop.
We go together, offer a deal.

05:18.301 --> 05:21.183
We won't press charges,
double the offer they ask for.

05:21.184 --> 05:24.146
But they can never come back.
- They'll believe that?

05:24.147 --> 05:27.109
- They'll believe $20,000 no-risk
dollars and a visit from a cop.

05:27.110 --> 05:29.833
- I'm sure you want this over
before you husband gets back.

05:31.114 --> 05:32.996
-[ Sighs ]

05:36.560 --> 05:38.561
I'll write you a check.

05:38.562 --> 05:42.925
I just can't believe how stupid
I was, how gullible. I...

05:42.926 --> 05:45.447
- Don't be too hard on yourself.
It happens.

05:45.448 --> 05:47.449
-It's not gonna happen again.

05:47.450 --> 05:50.333
The drawbridge is up.
No one gets in.

05:51.975 --> 05:54.456
- We can take care
of the rooster, too.

05:54.457 --> 05:56.899
It could have been worse.

05:56.900 --> 05:59.102
Could have been a real curse.

06:00.143 --> 06:04.827
♫♫

06:04.828 --> 06:07.469
-♫ She said careful ♫

06:07.470 --> 06:10.432
♫ Always careful ♫

06:10.433 --> 06:13.115
♫ Stay close and stay prepared ♫

06:13.116 --> 06:15.397
♫ One slip and you are theirs ♫

06:15.398 --> 06:16.799
♫ You gotta walk ♫

06:16.800 --> 06:19.361
- ♫ Walk on
well-lighted streets ♫

06:19.362 --> 06:22.645
- ♫ Walk on
well-lighted streets ♫

06:22.646 --> 06:24.567
- ♫ Walk on
well-lighted streets ♫

06:24.568 --> 06:28.811
- ♫ Look twice
at everyone I meet ♫

06:28.812 --> 06:31.815
♫♫

06:48.111 --> 06:49.592
-Doing the re-orders.

06:49.593 --> 06:51.594
Smudge sticks, candles.

06:51.595 --> 06:52.875
[ Sighs ]

06:52.876 --> 06:54.517
For Dixie and Gaya,
I was thinking

06:54.518 --> 06:56.999
maybe some New Age-y things,
Noho being what it is.

06:57.000 --> 06:59.882
I Ching coins, Books of Shadows,
incense.

06:59.883 --> 07:02.284
And then there's
a masonry supplies guy

07:02.285 --> 07:04.006
out in Simi Valley
who can do bulk crystals

07:04.007 --> 07:05.327
for half the price of
Bourget Brothers.

07:05.328 --> 07:08.932
[ Crackling ]

07:13.817 --> 07:15.778
-Did you hear that?

07:15.779 --> 07:17.099
-Hear what?

07:17.100 --> 07:19.421
-It's like mice in the walls.

07:19.422 --> 07:21.665
It's like a crackling.

07:25.108 --> 07:26.909
- You ought to
go see that Dr. White,

07:26.910 --> 07:31.914
'cause that sound...
I'm not hearing it.

07:31.915 --> 07:33.636
Really, honey.

07:33.637 --> 07:36.118
You better get yourself
checked out.

07:36.119 --> 07:38.320
-[ Sighs ]

07:38.321 --> 07:41.484
Okay.

07:41.485 --> 07:44.647
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:44.648 --> 07:46.008
-"And in the last sip,

07:46.009 --> 07:48.811
she turns the mug upside-down,

07:48.812 --> 07:51.453
coffee grounds
streak the saucer,

07:51.454 --> 07:56.780
finding future fortunes
in what others call a stain."

07:58.021 --> 08:01.984
[ Applause ]

08:01.985 --> 08:05.508
-[ Laughs ]

08:05.509 --> 08:06.989
-Beautiful, Jasmine.

08:06.990 --> 08:11.233
I am reminded of
my own grandmother's journey

08:11.234 --> 08:14.196
from the Craica in Baia Mare
to the streets of Marseille,

08:14.197 --> 08:17.760
and finally, to her family
waiting here in America.

08:17.761 --> 08:19.361
Where dreams come true.

08:19.362 --> 08:22.645
But for us, the promises
have been slow in coming.

08:22.646 --> 08:24.046
Stereotypes die hard,

08:24.047 --> 08:26.809
and as long as there are
Italian criminals,

08:26.810 --> 08:28.571
African-American crack dealers,

08:28.572 --> 08:31.133
Jewish pawnbrokers,

08:31.134 --> 08:33.736
those stereotypes will continue.

08:33.736 --> 08:36.619
Maybe they all change jobs
for a while.

08:36.620 --> 08:40.182
Jewish crack dealers, black
gangsters, Italian pawnbrokers.

08:40.183 --> 08:42.224
We would start to see things
differently.

08:42.225 --> 08:44.025
[ Light laughter ]

08:44.027 --> 08:45.628
And who are we?

08:45.629 --> 08:47.429
The people who fix your roof
so badly,

08:47.430 --> 08:51.153
it leaks worse in the next rain
than it did before you fixed it.

08:51.154 --> 08:55.718
The "tramps and thieves"...
The fortune tellers.

08:55.719 --> 08:59.922
Those of you here
who don't know our culture

08:59.923 --> 09:01.644
have most likely come today

09:01.645 --> 09:04.246
because you suspect
there's more to it than that,

09:04.247 --> 09:05.528
and you're right.

09:05.529 --> 09:08.851
Ours is a rich
and deep heritage.

09:08.852 --> 09:14.176
A heritage of persecution
and pride and poetry.

09:14.177 --> 09:18.141
[ Applause ]

09:22.706 --> 09:26.348
[ Siren wailing ]

09:26.349 --> 09:29.351
- Look, I didn't know
who else to call.

09:29.352 --> 09:30.713
-Thank you.

09:30.714 --> 09:33.155
-Thank you for coming.

09:33.156 --> 09:35.237
-Dolce &amp; Gabbana?

09:35.238 --> 09:37.439
What's that, $2,500
for a fucking dress?

09:37.440 --> 09:39.081
-I wanted to look nice for you.

09:39.082 --> 09:40.603
-You wanted the $2,500.

09:40.604 --> 09:43.365
- Please. I would have been lucky
to get $500.

09:43.366 --> 09:46.368
I'm... Well,
I was kind of counting on

09:46.369 --> 09:48.410
getting the job with you guys.

09:48.411 --> 09:50.573
I'm not exactly well-heeled.

09:50.574 --> 09:52.855
- Hand to mouth in Vegas,
I have been there.

09:52.856 --> 09:55.498
Look, shoplifting is not
a long-term solution.

09:55.499 --> 09:57.139
-Look, I was thinking.

09:57.140 --> 09:58.781
If I can stay here,

09:58.782 --> 10:00.823
I could be an asset
in the business.

10:00.824 --> 10:03.626
-We don't need a shoplifter.

10:03.627 --> 10:05.187
-Well, I can't go back.

10:05.188 --> 10:06.669
Greg recommended me to you

10:06.670 --> 10:09.191
so he could get rid of me
without any trouble.

10:09.192 --> 10:12.675
-What kind of trouble?

10:12.676 --> 10:14.356
-Wife trouble.

10:14.357 --> 10:15.959
-Ah.

10:21.444 --> 10:26.008
-You ever use, um...

10:26.009 --> 10:28.010
scopolamine?

10:28.011 --> 10:29.331
-What is that, like mouthwash?

10:29.332 --> 10:31.854
- [ Chuckles ]
It's a hypnotic drug.

10:31.855 --> 10:34.296
I blow it in your face,
you empty your bank account.

10:34.297 --> 10:36.378
Don't remember you did it.

10:36.379 --> 10:37.980
It's amazing stuff, really.

10:37.981 --> 10:40.262
You just got to be careful.

10:40.263 --> 10:42.385
I mean, I could show you.

10:44.427 --> 10:46.108
-Are you fucking kidding me?

10:46.109 --> 10:48.030
You're hustling me?

10:48.031 --> 10:52.035
- That's why you find me
so irresistible, right?

10:55.078 --> 10:57.279
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:57.280 --> 10:59.201
- What the fuck?
No rabbit stew?

10:59.202 --> 11:01.323
-Mm.

11:01.324 --> 11:04.086
I like that commercial you did,
huh?

11:04.087 --> 11:06.809
You're a young Robert De Niro.

11:06.810 --> 11:09.132
Very intense.

11:10.894 --> 11:12.054
Oh.

11:12.055 --> 11:14.938
How are you, darling, hmm?

11:16.700 --> 11:18.460
-Your mom didn't come?

11:18.461 --> 11:22.184
- Uh, she doesn't approve of
my cousin's cultural efforts.

11:22.185 --> 11:24.026
- Ah.
Well, I think it's important...

11:24.027 --> 11:26.268
Get out there, build bridges.

11:26.269 --> 11:29.311
- Want to give Fonso and me
a minute here, babe?

11:29.312 --> 11:30.593
-Sure.

11:30.594 --> 11:32.755
I'll go talk to the girls
about shoes.

11:32.756 --> 11:34.316
-Ooh.

11:34.317 --> 11:37.199
- See, that's the downside
to all this modernization.

11:37.200 --> 11:39.281
Now we get attitude.

11:39.282 --> 11:41.524
-Ah, it's a modern world.

11:41.525 --> 11:45.127
- I think we should talk
a little bit about Koreatown.

11:45.128 --> 11:48.291
I just want to make sure
we don't have a problem here.

11:50.293 --> 11:53.055
-Okay.

11:53.056 --> 11:56.499
I understand that you,
uh, you want to expand.

11:56.500 --> 11:58.781
You know, it's only natural.

11:58.782 --> 12:00.703
I understand.

12:00.704 --> 12:02.344
- And I'm glad
you can appreciate that.

12:02.345 --> 12:04.187
- I do.
I really do.

12:06.590 --> 12:08.831
Here's what works for me.

12:08.832 --> 12:12.755
I stay north of Olympic,
you take it south.

12:12.756 --> 12:15.718
You get the larger area.

12:15.719 --> 12:17.560
Only downside is,

12:17.561 --> 12:20.482
you got a lot of
Central American trade.

12:20.483 --> 12:25.087
Those curanderos
can get pretty intense.

12:25.088 --> 12:27.249
-I hate going into those places.

12:27.250 --> 12:29.051
-Now, the Koreans...

12:29.052 --> 12:32.855
They read your fortune
from your facial expressions.

12:32.856 --> 12:36.338
Fuckers don't even invest
in a deck of cards.

12:36.339 --> 12:38.300
- So, are they gonna be
a problem?

12:38.301 --> 12:41.344
- We got a guy in
the Businessmen's Association.

12:45.829 --> 12:48.150
[ Sighs ]

12:48.151 --> 12:50.352
So, we're good?

12:50.353 --> 12:52.795
-Yeah, we're good.

12:52.796 --> 12:55.037
- It wouldn't be a pachiv
without music.

12:55.038 --> 12:57.880
Please welcome
The Lemon Bucket Orchestra!

12:57.881 --> 13:01.443
[ Cheers and applause ]

13:01.444 --> 13:03.646
-[ Counting in native language ]

13:03.647 --> 13:06.650
♫♫

13:14.337 --> 13:15.938
-Support.

13:15.939 --> 13:18.060
What it is.

13:18.061 --> 13:20.102
-Michael's my cousin.

13:20.103 --> 13:21.584
-Can't you just write a check?

13:21.585 --> 13:22.985
-I wish.

13:22.986 --> 13:24.667
What's your excuse?

13:24.668 --> 13:26.789
- White T says it's good
for the image.

13:26.790 --> 13:29.191
I hear Bibi talking to
some of the other wives

13:29.192 --> 13:31.153
about the girls going to school.

13:31.154 --> 13:33.636
-It's the 21st century, Lou.

13:33.637 --> 13:36.398
- Some fancy-ass Harvard
or something.

13:36.399 --> 13:39.361
All the movie stars' kids
and all?

13:39.362 --> 13:41.684
-Well, it's a good school.

13:41.685 --> 13:43.686
My girls will get
a good education.

13:43.687 --> 13:46.489
-Right.

13:46.490 --> 13:47.930
So let me ask you.

13:47.931 --> 13:50.132
At this "good school"
they go to...

13:50.133 --> 13:52.575
They teach the girls how to give
a sweet blow job

13:52.576 --> 13:53.936
at the same time
they teach them to read,

13:53.937 --> 13:55.338
or is that a separate class?

14:08.672 --> 14:10.593
-[ Singing in native language ]

14:10.594 --> 14:13.597
♫♫

14:27.851 --> 14:29.933
-La de da.

14:34.618 --> 14:36.900
-[ Singing continues ]

14:43.386 --> 14:45.629
-Clean up in the bathroom.

14:55.398 --> 14:58.280
- In other words,
an auditory reversal

14:58.281 --> 15:00.082
in which the subject believes
that they are hearing voices

15:00.083 --> 15:03.125
from the future, from events
that haven't yet transpired.

15:03.126 --> 15:06.008
- So, you got a second opinion
from a podcast.

15:06.009 --> 15:08.971
That's [clears throat]
a little insulting.

15:08.972 --> 15:12.174
But, I mean, what's next,
a fucking TED Talk?

15:12.175 --> 15:14.817
- What's this guy talking about?
Sounds a lot like me.

15:14.818 --> 15:17.580
- Yeah. In med school, we used to
call it Intern's Disease.

15:17.581 --> 15:19.141
The interns
would get the symptoms

15:19.142 --> 15:20.583
of every disease
they read about.

15:20.584 --> 15:23.025
What you would have
is called WebMD Syndrome.

15:23.026 --> 15:24.707
Did you get as far as Othello?

15:24.708 --> 15:26.068
There's an Othello Syndrome

15:26.069 --> 15:28.190
related to certain kinds
of head trauma.

15:28.191 --> 15:30.112
It's also called
morbid jealousy.

15:30.113 --> 15:32.034
So in the last few days,
are you getting the suspicion

15:32.035 --> 15:33.756
that your wife's
being unfaithful?

15:33.757 --> 15:36.679
- Why would anyone
want to cheat on me?

15:36.680 --> 15:39.361
- Maybe you're not
everything she dreamed of.

15:39.362 --> 15:41.483
-[ Chuckles ]

15:41.484 --> 15:45.247
- You should know delusions
that follow organic insult

15:45.248 --> 15:47.329
are often empty of
psychological significance.

15:47.330 --> 15:49.612
Ideation is not necessarily
a direct result.

15:49.613 --> 15:51.534
Although, there is
an argument to be made

15:51.535 --> 15:53.255
for the epistemic nature
of some delusion.

15:53.256 --> 15:55.257
Is that high-tone
enough for you?

15:55.258 --> 15:57.379
-I'm having these symptoms.

15:57.380 --> 15:59.862
Colors are too bright.

15:59.863 --> 16:02.224
Food tastes wrong.

16:02.225 --> 16:05.588
I am hearing conversations
before they happen.

16:05.589 --> 16:09.071
You said on the phone you had
an alternative treatment.

16:09.072 --> 16:11.033
- First of all,
I want you to know

16:11.034 --> 16:14.076
that I believe you completely.

16:14.077 --> 16:17.079
You're getting glimpses
into the future.

16:17.080 --> 16:18.480
Time is out of joint,
as you put it.

16:18.481 --> 16:20.042
It's a lovely turn of phrase.

16:20.043 --> 16:24.046
The other day, I asked you
if you'd ever taken LSD.

16:24.047 --> 16:28.491
- Your medical advice
is for me to drop acid.

16:28.492 --> 16:31.253
- I am a big believer in locus.
In the Terminal Points...

16:31.254 --> 16:33.656
The Omega Point in
Quantum Physics, for example.

16:33.657 --> 16:36.579
It's where different
dimensions intersect.

16:36.580 --> 16:38.981
- So, the things
I'm experiencing...

16:38.982 --> 16:40.863
They're coming from
another dimension.

16:40.864 --> 16:42.985
- The things you are describing
are symptoms,

16:42.986 --> 16:44.867
as you learned
from the Internet,

16:44.868 --> 16:46.749
of mild traumatic brain injury.

16:46.750 --> 16:49.311
The question is not what they
are or even if they're real.

16:49.312 --> 16:51.033
The question is
how to make them stop.

16:51.034 --> 16:53.556
Do you want them to stop?
- And you're suggesting LSD.

16:53.557 --> 16:56.278
- No. My own research
has been with psilocybin.

16:56.279 --> 16:58.360
-I am already hearing things.

16:58.361 --> 17:00.042
I'm already seeing things.

17:00.043 --> 17:01.724
Isn't this putting gas
on a fire?

17:01.725 --> 17:04.126
- I want to take you back
to where things got fucked up

17:04.127 --> 17:06.127
and un-fuck them.

17:06.128 --> 17:09.531
I have seen marvelous results
with psilocybin

17:09.532 --> 17:11.213
in terms of shaking up the head.

17:11.214 --> 17:13.415
I would really love the chance
to rock your world.

17:13.415 --> 17:14.858
-Mm.

17:17.260 --> 17:22.625
You asked me if I ever did acid
when I was a kid.

17:22.626 --> 17:25.067
Did it a dozen times,
and I liked it.

17:25.068 --> 17:29.071
Gods were making love
in the clouds.

17:29.072 --> 17:33.516
The universe
seemed to make sense.

17:33.517 --> 17:36.719
Then one day,
I had this bad trip.

17:36.720 --> 17:39.281
I wanted to listen
to some music,

17:39.282 --> 17:41.924
and so I pulled out
Prince's "Parade."

17:41.925 --> 17:44.366
"Sometimes It Snows in April,"
right?

17:44.367 --> 17:47.329
And then I thought
if I listened to Prince,

17:47.330 --> 17:49.211
what about Simple Minds?

17:49.212 --> 17:50.933
What about
the "Amadeus" soundtrack?

17:50.934 --> 17:52.414
"Concerto in C
with Flute and Harp"?

17:52.415 --> 17:54.578
What about Van Halen? "1984?"

17:55.659 --> 17:59.302
I just stared at those records.

18:01.705 --> 18:03.626
I couldn't decide.

18:03.627 --> 18:05.107
I couldn't decide.

18:05.108 --> 18:08.430
For four hours,
I sat on the floor crying.

18:08.431 --> 18:13.155
-Well, like all great teachers,

18:13.156 --> 18:15.678
psychedelics inform by metaphor.

18:15.679 --> 18:16.999
-I was 17.

18:17.000 --> 18:18.841
My decisions were
Prince or Van Halen.

18:18.842 --> 18:21.403
Now my life is
a little more complicated.

18:21.404 --> 18:25.007
- I understand that, but look,
I really have seen this work.

18:25.008 --> 18:27.450
I think it could be
really helpful.

18:29.132 --> 18:33.376
- I think what would be helpful
is if I found another doctor.

18:34.818 --> 18:36.339
It's been a trip.

18:44.147 --> 18:46.348
-You ready to order?

18:46.349 --> 18:47.991
-I'm not hungry.

18:49.593 --> 18:51.914
But I'll take a refill.

18:51.915 --> 18:54.838
-Okay.

18:56.800 --> 19:01.003
- Is this Hawaiian Kona Reserve
made from a French press?

19:01.004 --> 19:03.526
- I'm pretty sure
it's just Folgers

19:03.527 --> 19:06.008
or whatever it is
we usually have.

19:06.009 --> 19:08.450
-Interesting.

19:08.451 --> 19:10.372
[ Laughing ] I like it.

19:10.373 --> 19:13.455
-Are you okay?

19:13.456 --> 19:16.298
-To be honest, I don't think so.

19:16.299 --> 19:18.621
-[ Chuckles ]

19:18.622 --> 19:20.543
I get it.

19:20.544 --> 19:24.507
Sometimes the best place
to be alone is in a crowd.

19:24.508 --> 19:26.949
Stay as long as you want.

19:26.950 --> 19:27.950
-Thank you.

19:27.951 --> 19:29.753
-Mm-hmm.

19:44.407 --> 19:46.810
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:52.255 --> 19:54.257
-Go.

19:56.900 --> 19:58.420
-Hey.

19:58.421 --> 19:59.902
-Hey.

19:59.903 --> 20:02.224
- So, do you still
have that Adderall?

20:02.225 --> 20:05.628
- Oh, the Adderall.
Uh, yeah, I do. At home, yeah.

20:05.629 --> 20:08.030
- I think, if you want, I could
get rid of some of it for you.

20:08.031 --> 20:10.272
Um...
Those jocks... they think...

20:10.273 --> 20:11.754
They think
it's performance-enhancing.

20:11.755 --> 20:13.516
We could probably get
like 10 bucks a pill.

20:13.517 --> 20:15.678
That is, if you don't need it
for your focus.

20:15.679 --> 20:17.479
- Oh, I don't have
a focus problem.

20:17.480 --> 20:18.721
I have a boredom problem.

20:18.722 --> 20:20.723
- [ Laughs ]
That's pretty tight.

20:20.724 --> 20:22.526
You should post that.

20:25.649 --> 20:27.850
The Drums.
I fucking love The Drums.

20:27.851 --> 20:29.411
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

20:29.412 --> 20:30.853
Um, they chill me out a lot
when I have, like,

20:30.854 --> 20:32.374
work to do or something.
[ Chuckles ]

20:32.375 --> 20:34.016
- Well, I-I only just
got into them.

20:34.017 --> 20:35.618
- Oh, you have to hear
"Down By The Water."

20:35.619 --> 20:37.980
It is so romantic,
you won't believe it.

20:37.981 --> 20:40.984
♫♫

20:50.273 --> 20:55.758
- ♫ If you fall asleep
down by the water ♫

20:55.759 --> 21:00.082
♫ Baby, I'll carry you
all the way home ♫

21:00.083 --> 21:02.525
-I better get back.

21:02.526 --> 21:07.730
- ♫ If you fall asleep
down by the water ♫

21:07.731 --> 21:13.135
♫ Baby, I'll carry you
all the way home ♫

21:13.136 --> 21:15.898
♫♫

21:15.899 --> 21:20.102
♫ Everybody's got to
love someone ♫

21:20.103 --> 21:21.825
[ Wood chipper buzzing ]

21:26.389 --> 21:27.631
[ Cellphone chimes ]

21:40.884 --> 21:43.887
♫♫

22:05.789 --> 22:07.230
-[ Sighs ]

22:11.915 --> 22:14.116
[ Cellphone rings ]

22:14.117 --> 22:15.437
Yeah.

22:15.438 --> 22:16.999
-Hey. It's Fonso.

22:17.000 --> 22:18.641
I'm at your Van Nuys place.

22:18.642 --> 22:21.564
What used to be
your Van Nuys place.

22:21.565 --> 22:24.326
You suffered enough
for your sister's fuck-up.

22:24.327 --> 22:26.128
I'm giving the place
back to you.

22:26.129 --> 22:28.370
Listen.
One thing about the parlor.

22:28.371 --> 22:30.252
You're gonna have to use
my cousin Fabiana.

22:30.253 --> 22:32.895
-Your cousin?
-We call her
The Crystal Ball Buster.

22:32.896 --> 22:34.537
Just so you know.
- What does that mean?

22:34.538 --> 22:37.379
- It means she's your headache
now, not mine.

22:37.380 --> 22:39.862
And again, you're welcome.

22:39.863 --> 22:42.866
♫♫

23:37.881 --> 23:39.121
-Now, here at Muirwood,

23:39.122 --> 23:41.524
we offer a progressive
education.

23:41.525 --> 23:43.726
That does not mean
an easy education.

23:43.727 --> 23:45.327
It does not mean no education.

23:45.328 --> 23:48.131
What it does mean
is a valued education.

23:52.215 --> 23:54.336
- Boy or girl?
- I'm sorry?

23:54.337 --> 23:56.499
- Is yours a boy or girl?
- Oh, boy.

23:56.500 --> 23:59.101
- Now let's take a look
at our gymnasium. Follow me.

23:59.102 --> 24:01.223
- Wild one?
- Oh, he can be.

24:01.224 --> 24:02.506
- [ Laughs ]
- Dad.

24:03.787 --> 24:05.988
I thought you said
you weren't coming today.

24:05.989 --> 24:08.632
-[ Sighs ]

24:10.353 --> 24:11.954
How was it?

24:11.955 --> 24:13.556
-How was what?

24:13.557 --> 24:16.478
- Simi Valley.
The new crystals.

24:16.479 --> 24:19.041
- Oh, I got 20 pounds
in the back seat of the car.

24:19.042 --> 24:22.444
If they sell, we get
a better rate at 50 pounds.

24:22.445 --> 24:23.686
What are you cooking?

24:23.687 --> 24:25.768
-I am trying to see

24:25.769 --> 24:29.692
if I can make better paprikas
than Rita.

24:29.693 --> 24:32.935
- Hmm,
you seem decidedly chipper.

24:32.936 --> 24:36.779
-Crystal discounts? I Ching?

24:36.780 --> 24:39.061
Those are problems for Fonso
from now on.

24:39.062 --> 24:41.183
We are out of that business.

24:41.184 --> 24:43.946
-You found something.

24:43.947 --> 24:47.469
- Nadine Davies
does not have kids.

24:47.470 --> 24:48.991
-No.

24:48.992 --> 24:51.634
- Then why is she
shopping at toy stores,

24:51.635 --> 24:55.558
going to Little League fields,
and taking school tours?

24:55.559 --> 24:56.959
-School tours?

24:56.960 --> 24:59.522
-I saw her at Muirwood.

24:59.523 --> 25:02.245
-Jesus Christ.

25:04.007 --> 25:06.288
That is so sad.

25:06.289 --> 25:08.891
-Tragic.

25:08.892 --> 25:11.213
Potentially.

25:11.214 --> 25:12.415
[ Chuckles ]

25:16.500 --> 25:18.942
[ Crackling ]

25:33.997 --> 25:36.359
[ Floorboards cracking ]

25:55.018 --> 25:58.021
[ Crackling continues ]

26:01.785 --> 26:04.707
-Charlie?

26:04.708 --> 26:07.069
- Sorry to come so early,
but Eduardo...

26:07.070 --> 26:09.112
He said to come
as soon as we could.

26:11.434 --> 26:13.717
-You do floors?

26:22.606 --> 26:23.886
-I wish more people had come.

26:23.887 --> 26:26.168
More of our people
and more gadje.

26:26.169 --> 26:28.491
-It was a good event.

26:28.492 --> 26:31.494
I could have done with
less of the poetry bullshit,

26:31.495 --> 26:33.215
but whatever.

26:33.216 --> 26:36.258
I got a busy day today,
so just tell me what you want.

26:36.259 --> 26:39.261
- I'm following up on
our conversation yesterday.

26:39.262 --> 26:40.262
When you were leaving.

26:40.263 --> 26:41.383
-Enlighten me.

26:41.384 --> 26:43.065
I was kind of in a state.

26:43.066 --> 26:45.668
- You said, "If there's anything
I can do to help..."

26:45.669 --> 26:48.150
So I was just...

26:48.151 --> 26:50.312
-He wants your money.

26:50.313 --> 26:52.835
-It's for a good cause, Bibio.

26:52.836 --> 26:55.037
We're starting a fund.

26:55.038 --> 27:00.242
Special grants for Roma families
bringing up disabled children.

27:00.243 --> 27:02.124
-In my day, we put them to work.

27:02.125 --> 27:03.606
-Eh, can't do that anymore, Ma.

27:03.607 --> 27:04.887
-He's ashamed of us.

27:04.888 --> 27:06.690
He thinks he's superior.

27:08.171 --> 27:09.411
-That's not true.

27:09.412 --> 27:11.373
All I want
is to build community.

27:11.374 --> 27:13.055
Put out a positive image.

27:13.056 --> 27:16.739
Let people know we produce poets
as well as pickpockets.

27:16.740 --> 27:20.382
- He insults us
and then he asks for money.

27:20.383 --> 27:22.064
Dosta.

27:22.065 --> 27:23.425
Dosta!

27:23.426 --> 27:25.108
-Fonso.

27:28.712 --> 27:30.192
-Has anybody seen my phone?

27:30.193 --> 27:31.714
-Ah, girls. Hi!

27:31.715 --> 27:32.915
Come. Have breakfast.

27:32.916 --> 27:34.116
-I'm not hungry.

27:34.117 --> 27:35.277
-Drina, you have to eat.

27:35.278 --> 27:37.119
- I don't have time.
- Oh, no?

27:37.120 --> 27:39.321
- I have a quiz first period,
and Lindsey's giving us a ride.

27:39.322 --> 27:41.243
- I could drive you.
- Dad, no.

27:41.244 --> 27:44.086
I hate showing up in your car.
Everybody talks about it.

27:44.087 --> 27:45.728
- The fuck is wrong
with a Bentley?

27:45.729 --> 27:47.329
[ Cellphone chimes ]
- Shit. She's already outside.

27:47.330 --> 27:49.131
- Language.
- We got to go.

27:49.132 --> 27:50.693
- No, no.
Have your breakfast first.

27:50.694 --> 27:53.096
-Lala! Jesus.

27:54.898 --> 27:56.418
-Love you, baby.

27:56.419 --> 27:58.901
-Fonso.

27:58.902 --> 28:01.704
You need to have control
over Drina.

28:01.705 --> 28:04.146
- Eh, she's 14.
Give her a break.

28:04.147 --> 28:06.348
-Oh, no, she doesn't
need a break.
[ Doorbell rings ]

28:06.349 --> 28:08.430
She needs a firm hand.

28:08.431 --> 28:10.713
Now what?

28:10.714 --> 28:13.395
-That, uh, gadje's kid's here.

28:13.396 --> 28:15.838
-Hey. Kid.

28:15.839 --> 28:16.999
What the hell?

28:17.000 --> 28:18.400
Huh?

28:18.401 --> 28:19.722
You with your dad?

28:19.723 --> 28:21.724
-No, just... just me.

28:21.725 --> 28:23.686
- Everything okay?
He didn't have another...

28:23.687 --> 28:25.447
Another one of the things
with his head?

28:25.448 --> 28:27.249
- Yeah, he's... he's fine.
Great.

28:27.250 --> 28:28.891
I was just...
I was wondering...

28:28.892 --> 28:32.935
Um, could I talk to just...

28:32.936 --> 28:34.176
Have a second with you?

28:34.177 --> 28:35.619
Just me and you.

28:37.180 --> 28:38.981
- Man to man.
- Yeah.

28:38.982 --> 28:41.183
Yeah.

28:41.184 --> 28:42.705
-Sure.

28:42.706 --> 28:45.588
So, what's going on with you,
hm?

28:45.589 --> 28:48.030
- Well, you know,
I was just wondering, um...

28:48.031 --> 28:50.032
What...
What I was gonna ask Mrs. Marks

28:50.033 --> 28:52.354
was that there's this...
There's this girl at my school,

28:52.355 --> 28:54.236
and...
- Hey, hey, hey.

28:54.237 --> 28:58.721
We don't arrange for any, uh,
operations, anything like that.

28:58.722 --> 29:00.362
-No.

29:00.363 --> 29:01.564
No, no, no, no, no, no.

29:01.565 --> 29:03.165
That's...
That's not what I meant.

29:03.166 --> 29:05.608
It's... It's just that I kind of
like her, you know?

29:05.609 --> 29:08.531
Like, a lot.
And, um...

29:08.532 --> 29:11.133
I'm not really sure. You know,
sometimes it seems like she...

29:11.134 --> 29:13.015
She kind of likes me back
a little bit.

29:13.016 --> 29:14.777
Just the tiniest bit.
But I want to...

29:14.778 --> 29:17.139
I don't know
how to find out if...

29:17.140 --> 29:18.741
-Love's a bitch.

29:18.742 --> 29:21.585
Come on.
I got something for you.

29:25.549 --> 29:27.189
- Last night
at 4:00 in the morning,

29:27.190 --> 29:28.551
I moved the furniture
in my office

29:28.552 --> 29:30.072
and tore up the floor

29:30.073 --> 29:32.636
looking for a sound
that wasn't there.

29:34.758 --> 29:37.239
You said you wanted a chance
to rock my world?

29:37.240 --> 29:40.322
Well, I would say my world
has already been rocked.

29:40.323 --> 29:46.248
- You had mentioned looking for
a second opinion.

29:46.249 --> 29:49.692
-Maybe we should just do this.

29:49.693 --> 29:52.335
-Okay.

29:53.537 --> 29:55.498
There's something I find
both more...

29:55.499 --> 29:59.141
I don't know... therapeutic
and, uh, I don't know...

29:59.142 --> 30:03.666
Organic about the traditional
method of ingestion.

30:03.667 --> 30:07.870
Uh, I'm afraid there might be
some vomiting involved.

30:07.871 --> 30:10.713
- I always had a tough time
with that part.

30:10.714 --> 30:12.354
[ Clears throat ]

30:12.355 --> 30:13.996
- You might want to
call your wife,

30:13.997 --> 30:16.560
let her know that
you will be here overnight.

30:21.164 --> 30:23.046
[ Clears throat ]

30:25.128 --> 30:30.052
You do not want to trip
without the warmth of vinyl.

30:30.053 --> 30:31.574
Dual moving coil cartridge.

30:31.575 --> 30:33.095
Decent speakers.

30:33.096 --> 30:36.258
I have got that
Mozart "Concerto in C"

30:36.259 --> 30:38.140
and I've got Miles, of course.

30:38.141 --> 30:41.063
And I've got Ornette Coleman for
the patients that piss me off.

30:41.064 --> 30:45.067
But given your history
with choice,

30:45.068 --> 30:48.711
I think we should
just stick with Mozart.

30:48.712 --> 30:51.554
Okay, it takes about 45 minutes
to kick in.

30:51.555 --> 30:53.876
- I remember.
- Um, you're gonna be fine, okay?

30:53.877 --> 30:56.078
So just stay here and relax.

30:56.079 --> 30:57.920
The record will just keep going.

30:57.921 --> 30:59.922
Unless you actually stop it,

30:59.923 --> 31:01.644
the arm lifts up
and goes back to the beginning

31:01.645 --> 31:03.405
and the concerto
just starts again.

31:03.406 --> 31:05.447
It's a miracle of
1950s technology.

31:05.448 --> 31:09.091
Uh, so, I will be back before
you can say Jerry Garcia, okay?

31:09.092 --> 31:10.452
So just sit.

31:10.453 --> 31:13.456
[ Concerto plays ]

31:21.144 --> 31:23.507
-[ Sighs ]

31:39.643 --> 31:42.245
[ Retches ]

31:47.130 --> 31:50.333
[ Laughs ]

31:56.019 --> 31:58.060
Um.

31:58.061 --> 32:01.064
[ Concerto continues ]

32:16.239 --> 32:19.082
[ Chuckles ]

32:29.933 --> 32:33.136
[ Vinyl scratches ]

32:37.020 --> 32:38.822
[ Music stops ]

32:45.148 --> 32:46.509
[ Laughs ]

32:46.510 --> 32:48.632
[ Concerto plays ]

33:05.368 --> 33:07.531
[ Alarm blares ]

33:14.257 --> 33:17.740
-Sorry.

33:17.741 --> 33:20.103
- I'm so sorry.
We're gonna have to go.

33:21.865 --> 33:23.827
Charlie?

33:43.206 --> 33:45.167
-Help me mulch.

33:45.168 --> 33:47.850
And don't put it on too thick.

33:47.851 --> 33:50.172
You'll suffocate the plant.

33:50.173 --> 33:52.575
I'm all about
the brighter bloom.

33:52.576 --> 33:55.618
So, what are you looking for?

33:55.619 --> 33:58.021
-A brighter bloom.

33:59.102 --> 34:01.103
-How many mushrooms?

34:01.104 --> 34:03.065
-A lot.

34:03.066 --> 34:05.588
-And you saw something.

34:05.589 --> 34:07.229
-A ring of fire.

34:07.230 --> 34:10.351
- [ Deep voice ]
"Hello, I'm Johnny Cash."

34:10.353 --> 34:11.873
-Cards on the table?

34:11.875 --> 34:13.795
I'm a carny.

34:13.797 --> 34:15.317
I'm bullshit.

34:15.318 --> 34:17.880
- So far,
we're in complete agreement.

34:17.880 --> 34:19.681
-Something's happening to me.

34:19.683 --> 34:22.284
- You're on mushrooms.
What'd you expect?

34:22.284 --> 34:24.647
-I'm hearing things.

34:24.648 --> 34:26.208
Getting glimpses.

34:26.208 --> 34:28.931
Stuff that's about to happen.

34:28.931 --> 34:32.614
- [ Chuckles ]
A fake psychic, real visions.

34:32.616 --> 34:35.697
That'd be a cosmic joke
on God's part.

34:35.699 --> 34:40.463
Man, for you, that would be
serious world-view fuck.

34:42.746 --> 34:44.627
Cosmic joke or karma...

34:44.628 --> 34:47.949
Either way, you're in trouble.

34:47.951 --> 34:50.072
Reminds me of those cartoons.

34:50.072 --> 34:51.353
Sylvester the Cat...

34:51.353 --> 34:52.715
He's got an angel
on one shoulder

34:52.716 --> 34:54.076
and a devil on the other,

34:54.077 --> 34:56.639
and one's telling him
to kill Tweety

34:56.639 --> 34:59.482
and the other one's telling him
to love all the animals.

35:01.084 --> 35:04.246
- It's in a cat's nature
to kill a bird.

35:04.247 --> 35:06.248
-Doesn't make it right.

35:06.249 --> 35:08.771
-What should I do?

35:08.772 --> 35:11.133
-You got to decide, man.

35:11.134 --> 35:13.375
-Decide?

35:13.376 --> 35:15.017
-Who you're gonna listen to.

